const overview = `Mustang, a remote region in northern Nepal, is renowned for its unique culture, stunning landscapes, and ancient monasteries. This high-altitude desert region offers a glimpse into a bygone era, with its well-preserved Tibetan Buddhist traditions and breathtaking scenery. The region is home to the famous Mustang Valley, a UNESCO World Heritage Site known for its ancient rock paintings and mud-brick villages. Mustang is characterized by its arid, high-altitude landscapes, including deep gorges, barren hills, and towering peaks.

Journey into the “Last Forbidden Kingdom” and explore the walled city of Lo-Manthang. The trek offers a unique blend of adventure and spirituality, characterized by trans-Himalayan desert landscapes, rich Tibetan Buddhist culture, and panoramic views of the Nilgiri, Annapurna, and Dhaulagiri ranges. It is a restricted trekking region, ensuring fewer trekkers and preserving its authenticity and exclusivity.`;
